# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 7 (Performance / Caching / Scalability)

Spec: `docs/09_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_07_PERFORMANCE.md`

## Rules

- Prefer Server Components; keep Client Components as interactive islands.
- Memoize hot loaders with React `cache()` within a request — do not invent stale tenant business caches.
- Parallelize independent awaits (`Promise.all`); avoid sequential waterfalls.
- Cap portfolio/list loops; use `mapWithConcurrency` for bounded fan-out.
- Lazy-load heavy workspaces via `src/components/performance/lazy-workspaces.tsx` when UX-safe.
- Skip overlapping job executions (`hasRunningJobExecution`) unless force-run.
- Never weaken auth, RBAC, RLS, or Paddle billing behaviour.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 7 work.
